## [ Build Artifacts ]
bin/
obj/
[Rr]elease/
[Dd]ebug/
x64/
x86/
bld/
[Log]s/
.db
.db-wal
.db-shm

## [ Specialized Build Folders ]
# Used by MSBuild for publishing
publish/
# Used by Azure Functions Core Tools
.azurefunctions/
# ASP.NET Core cache
.kpro_cache/

## [ User-Specific Files ]
*.user
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates
# Rider / Resharper
.idea/
*.sln.iml
# Visual Studio Code
.vscode/
!.vscode/settings.json
!.vscode/tasks.json
!.vscode/launch.json
!.vscode/extensions.json

## [ Visual Studio Specific ]
.vs/
*.suo
*.user
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates

## [ NuGet Packages ]
# Most projects use 'dotnet restore', so we ignore the local packages folder
*.nupkg
**/packages/*
!**/packages/build/
# Specifically for NuGet's global cache
node_modules/

## [ Environment & Secrets ]
# Do NOT commit secrets
.env
*.dev.secrets
appsettings.Development.json
# Note: Some teams prefer to commit appsettings.Development.json 
# but keep actual secrets in 'User Secrets' or environment variables.

## [ Testing ]
TestResults/
*.sequenced

## [ Operating System Files ]
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
